article.headline: New Hampshire 64, UMBC 51
article.story: DURHAM, N.H. (AP) -- Jermaine Anderson scored 24 points and Blagoj Janev had 23 to lead New Hampshire to a 64-51 win over Maryland-Baltimore County on Sunday. The win, combined with Hartford's loss to Vermont, gave the Wildcats (10-19, 6-10 America East) the seventh seed in the conference tournament. The Retrievers will be fifth. Brian Hodges scored 20 points for UMBC (11-18, 7-9) and Mike Housman had 10 points and seven rebounds. New Hampshire had a season-high 39 rebounds to the Retrievers' 24.
